3 types of INPUT DATA sources
  • 1) publicly available and no auth required. Used directly in the pipeline.
  • 2) private data that is pre-processed by lab pipelines where the processed data can be made public
  • 3) Private data that is used directly in the pipeline via some login credentials (i.e TCIA/NBIA or EGA) but the data cannot be made available to public.
1) Nothing to do from a development side of things<br style="font-size: 13px;">- as long as the pipeline can run and its implemented to grab the data from the source<br style="font-size: 13px;">

Development Requirements that apply to all of  1), 2), 3)
- only need to make sure that theres internet access 
- kube pod that the download occurs in needs to have enough local storage to store the incoming data

2) Multi-step process for this edge-case<br style="font-size: 13px;">- pipeline to "pre-process" the data must be git version controlled <br style="font-size: 13px;">- the details of the preprocessing pipeline should be described in the main pipeline letting users know what repo to refer to <br style="font-size: 13px;">- Documentation needs to be written to let curators know that if their pipeline falls in this category, they have to give us extra information<br style="font-size: 13px;">so we can arrange for this edge-case<br style="font-size: 13px;"><br style="font-size: 13px;">Best case scenario: Pipeline is uploaded with the processed data output to Zenodo and that is used as input (wget/curl) in the main pipeline

3) Two possible cases here:<br style="font-size: 13px;"><br style="font-size: 13px;">3.1) Public data and we have credentials that we can use (i.e NBIA/EGA)<br style="font-size: 13px;">-  we can just incorporate that into the pipeline where the data is downloaded but not stored nor made available to public<br style="font-size: 13px;"><br style="font-size: 13px;">3.2) Some sort of private data delivered from a lab or something<br style="font-size: 13px;">- set up a gcs bucket (no public access) that the kubernetes cluster has access to <br style="font-size: 13px;">- Need to let users know that this is private data and users wont have access to it
